        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 12:45PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1244 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Buffalo, or near Lafayette, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fredonia, Post Oak Forks, Lakeview, La Fayette, Veasey Creek Park,
Denson, White Plains, Amity Park, Five Points, Lafayette, Lanett,
Stroud, Standing Rock, Stroud Creek, Welch, Penton, Buffalo, Southern
Harbor, and Huguley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
